new Bias(source: "http://www.huffingtonpost.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "The Huffington Post is an American online news aggregator and blog that has both localized and international editions founded by Arianna Huffington; Kenneth Lerer; Andrew Breitbart; and Jonah Peretti. Huffington Post displays left wing bias through story selection and word choices. Not evidence based on some scientific issues; but generally well sourced overall. (5/13/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "https://www.inequalitymedia.org/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Inequality Mediaproduces original film and video; share theircontent through social media and media outlets to raise awareness about the issues; and partner with leading organizations to provide an avenue through which viewers can engage; mobilize; and take action against inequality. Inequality Media has a left wing political bias; but produces videos that are well sourced and factual. (12/15/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "http://inthesetimes.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "In These Times is an American politically progressive/democratic socialist monthly magazine of news and opinion published by the Institute for Public Affairs in Chicago; Illinois. This is a very solid source for well written factual stories. (5/13/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "https://www.jacobinmag.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Jacobin is a left-wing quarterly magazine based in New York. It claims to bea leading voice of the American left; offering socialist perspectives on politics; economics; and culture. It isbiased in reporting; but very well written and sourced."),
new Bias(source: "http://jezebel.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Jezebel is not really a political news source. It is more opinion based that is focused on entertainment news. Jezebel isbiased in favor of liberal causes through story choices and wording. (7/27/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.lavendermagazine.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Lavender is a biweekly magazine; part of Lavender Media; published in Minneapolis; Minnesota for the gay; lesbian; bisexual; and transgender community. Lavender has a liberal political affiliation through story choices and is well sourced."),
new Bias(source: "Left Action", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Left Action is a network of over 1;000;000 activists committed to making a difference and fighting for progressive causes. Sporadically provides news that is mostly factual with left bias in wording and reporting."),
new Bias(source: "https://leftfootforward.org/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Left Foot Forward (LFF) is a left wing political blog in the UK; established in 2009.It regards as sister blogs ThinkProgress in the United States; and Chifley in Australia. LFF has a left bias in reporting choices and wording. Most articles are sourced properly and for the most part are factual."),
new Bias(source: "http://leftoverrights.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Left Over Rights is a news and opinion blog with a left wing bias in reporting. Many headlines contain loaded words as do the articles themselves. Most stories are sourced to credible information; however some are pure speculation such as discussing the Presidents health problems; for which there is not evidence. Based on this we give a mixed factual reporting rating."),
new Bias(source: "https://www.leftscoop.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "LeftScoop is a news and opinion website with a borderline extreme left bias in reporting. Virtually every headline utilizes sensational loaded words that induce clicking (Clickbait). The content of articles; however; are typically sourced to credible mainstream media sources; with LeftScoop writers providing opinion about the news story. This opinion is always pro-left and anti-right. Although they source to credible information and we cannot find any instances of failed fact checks; we still rate them mixed for factual reporting based on strong opinions that can be distracting and misleading from the facts."),
new Bias(source: "http://www.leftsideofhistory.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Left Side of History is essentially a strong left leaning opinion blog. According to the website; Left Side of History describes itself as a new blog intelligently reporting and analyzing current events through a leftist lens. We are trying to combat the digitalmedia trends of clickbait and unsubstantiated; misleading news with nosubstance. The stories are all biased in favor of the left; which they make clear in the description. There is minimal use of loaded words and most entries are sourced to reasonable media. We give this source a mixed rating for factual reporting due to it being mostly opinion based."),
new Bias(source: "http://www.lgbtqnation.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "LGBTQ Nation is an online news magazine; reporting on issues relevant to the lesbian; gay; bisexual; transgender; queer community. LGBTQ Nation is factually sourced and uses minimal loaded words. Has a strong left wing political affiliation through story choices and advocacy. (2/9/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.liberalamerica.org/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Liberal America claims to be the only place on the web that is devoted solely to all things liberal. This is a very fair claim and is accurate. Most headlines are sensationalized and the content of articles contains loaded emotional words. Liberal America sources where they are getting information from; but many times it is from other left wing or questionable sources. Therefore; we assign a mixed factual rating. (11/18/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "http://samuel-warde.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Liberals Unite is a well established very liberally biased news and opinion website. Liberals Unite has a strong left wing bias through reporting and word choices. (10/30/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "https://www.liberationnews.org/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Liberation News is a socialist print newspaper that appears irregularly as well as awebsite that delivers news.Liberation News calls for a socialist revolution in North America and the world to end the dictatorial power of the wealthy; for a redistribution of the wealth; and for a planned economy run to meet human and environmental needs. Liberation news has a left wing socialist political bias in reporting and affiliation; however most content is well sourced to reliable media outlets. (5/5/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://littlegreenfootballs.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Little Green Footballs (LGF) is an American political blog run by web designer Charles Johnson. In its beginning years; the site had a right-wing orientation and known for its advocacy of the War on Terrorism and the Iraq War; as well its strident criticism of political Islam. The blog moved away from the right around 2009. Currently; the blog has a left-wing bias in reporting and story choices. They also occasionally publish unverified stories such as this one."),
new Bias(source: "http://mashable.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Mashable is a news and opinion site that focuses mostly on social media and technology. When covering political issues they have a left bias in story selection."),
new Bias(source: "http://meanlefthook.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Mean Left Hook is an unashamedly left bias site heavily loaded the most sensationalistic and confrontational rhetoric of the left. The articles; if they can honestly be called articles in the usual sense; are little more than the type of rants against the right you would find on a Facebook page. Mean Left Hook does in fact have a FB page which is primarily links to their articles sprinkled with pro left cartoons and memes."),
new Bias(source: "http://www.mediaite.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Mediaite is a liberal news and opinion blog covering politics and entertainment in the media industry. It is the flagship blog of Abrams Media; a ring of blogs run by ABC legal analyst Dan Abrams. Mediaite presents news with aleft wing bias in reporting choices. Although they publish mostly stories that favor the left; they do source their content well. (8/21/2016) Updated (5/12/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://mediamatters.org/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Media Matters for America is a politically progressive media watchdog in the United States. The organization has a stated mission of comprehensively monitoring; analyzing; and correcting conservative misinformation in the U.S. media.Set up as a tax-exempt; nonprofit organization; MMfA was founded in 2004 by journalist and political activist David Brock as a counterweight to the conservative Media Research Center.It is known for its aggressive criticism of conservative journalists and media outlets; including its War on Fox News. According to Politifact Media Matters has been factual in reporting. (5/13/2016) Updated (4/24/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "https://www.merryjane.com/", factuality: "HIGH (No pun intended)", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Merry Jane is a website all about Marijuana (Cannabis). It provides news on marijuana legislation and lifestyle. It has a left wing political bias in reporting and political affiliation. All articles are well sourced and factual. This is a solid resource for all things cannabis."),
new Bias(source: "http://www.miaminewtimes.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Miami New Times (MNT) is the online version of the local newspaper of the same name. Most of the sites content is; as one would expect; Miami specific. It does carry some political content; however; and it is on that content alone that MNT is rated. The political stories are factual and sourced well enough; but the information is presented and weighted with a decidedly left slant. (D. Kelley)"),
new Bias(source: "https://www.middleeastmonitor.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "The Middle East Monitor (MEMO) is a not-for-profitpress monitoring organization; founded on 1 July 2009.MEMO is largely focused on the IsraeliPalestinian conflict but writes about other issues in the Middle East as well. According to Ehud Rosen; MEMO generally supports Islamist positions within Palestinian politics.According to Andrew Gilligan; the Middle East Monitor promotes a strongly pro-Muslim Brotherhood and pro-Hamas viewpoint. Anshel Pfeffer described MEMO as a conspiracy theory-peddling anti-Israel organisation. Our review shows that the Middle East Monitor has a left wing bias in the use of loaded words and also in story choices that promote Islamic positions.We could not find any instances of the Middle East Monitor failing fact checks; but they do sometimes source to questionable media outlets and hence garner a Mixed factual rating. (D. Van Zandt)"),
new Bias(source: "http://modernliberals.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Modern Liberals is a website dedicated to liberal news. This source presents news and opinions with a left wing bias in reporting choices and the use of emotive words. Modern Liberals also publishes satire and fake news that is clearly labeled as such. They currently have a questionable article up claiming several news sources to be fake. While some on this list are questionable and some just biased like the Palmer Report and Breitbart; none of them are fake news and usually have information rooted in fact. Modern Liberals is on the borderline of being a questionable website and will be monitored."),
new Bias(source: "http://mondoweiss.net/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Mondoweissis a news website that is co-edited by journalists Philip Weiss and Adam Horowitz. It is a part of the Center for Economic Research and Social Change. According to the editors; Mondoweiss is a news website devoted to covering American foreign policy in the Middle East; chiefly from a progressive Jewish perspective. Its founder describes himself as progressive and anti-Zionist. Overall; Mondoweiss is well sourced and factual. Headlines generally match the content of articles and loaded words are at a minimum. This source has a left wing bias in reporting and through its support of Palestine and general liberal causes. (3/4/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.motherjones.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Mother Jonesis a politically progressive American magazine reporting on politics; the environment; human rights; and culture. Mother Jones is published by the Foundation for National Progress (FNP); a nonprofit 501(c)(3) organization. Mother Jones has been a finalist for 31 National Magazine Awards; winning seven times. Mother Jones provides in depth journalism that mostlyfavors the political left. We cannot find any evidence of Mother Jones making false claims and when in error they correct appropriately. This is a factual source that is always well sourced. (5/13/2016) Updated (4/25/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://front.moveon.org/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "MoveOn.org is an American; non-profit; progressive public policy advocacy group and political action committee.Formed in 1998 in response to the impeachment of President Bill Clinton by the U.S. House of Representatives; MoveOn.org has raised millions of dollars for candidates it identifies as progressives in the United States. Strong left wing bias with reporting and has an unproven claim according to Snopes."),
new Bias(source: "http://www.msmagazine.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Ms. is an American liberal feminist magazine co-founded by second-wave feminists and sociopolitical activists Gloria Steinem and Dorothy Pitman Hughes. Ms. occasionally uses loaded words in headlines and articles. They typically report factually with backing sources. We rate them left biased based on political ideology and affiliation through there promotion of feminism."),
new Bias(source: "http://nap-sack.org/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Nap-Sack bills itself as an alternative social media site open to the world at large to voice their opinions on anything; social and political issues; science; spiritualism; etc. In this it largely succeeds as there are numerous options for visitors to start petitions; comment on the blogs and start or join discussion groups. The blogs on the site were a mixed bag; running the gamut from left bias political commentary; to UFOs; to spirituality. Other than the blog commentary; Nap-Sack is a-political as it encourages visitors to speak their mind regardless of their political and social views. They also offer links to a variety of news sources from Russia Today to Reuters. Nap-Sack; as it is a social media site and doesnt pretend to be anything else; does not easily fit in any of the usual MBFC categories. It is Pro-Science in some regards; Conspiracy-Pseudoscience in others; and somewhat Questionable as well. It earned a Left Bias strictly from the political content of the blogs. While I wouldnt recommend Nap-Sack as a news source I do applaud their effort to provide an open forum for the world to speak out. (D. Kelley)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.nationofchange.org/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Nation of Change is a 501(c) nonprofit news and activism organization founded in 2011 and based out of Albuquerque; New Mexico. Nation of Change provides a free daily newsletter with articles from progressive writers and initiates activist calls to action. Nation of Change does not always support the consensus of science. (5/13/2016) Updated (2/24/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "https://newint.org/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Established in 1973. New Internationalist (NI) is an independent; non-profit; publishing co-operative; based in Oxford; United Kingdom. Predominantly known for its monthly independent magazine; it describes itself as existing to cover stories the mainstream media sidestep and provide alternative perspectives on todays global critical issues. New Internationalist presents news with a moderate left wing bias throughreporting choices. NI always sources to credible information. (5/13/2016) Updated (4/25/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://newpol.org/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "New Politics is an independent socialist journal founded in 1961.While it is inclusive of articles from a variety of left-of-center positions; the publication leans strongly toward a democratic Marxist perspective; placing it typically to the left of the liberal or social democratic views. Strong journalism and factually sourced. (8/17/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "https://newrepublic.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "The New Republic is a liberal American magazine of commentary on politics and the arts published since 1914; with major influence on American political and cultural thinking. Founded in 1914 by major leaders of the Progressive Movement it attempted to find a balance between a progressivism focused on humanitarianism and moral passion; and on the other hand sought a basis in scientific analysis of social issues. New Republic has produced quality journalism for over a century."),
new Bias(source: "http://www.newstatesman.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "The New Statesman is a British political and cultural magazine published in London. Founded as a weekly review of politics and literature on 12 April 1913; it was connected then with Sidney and Beatrice Webb and other leading members of the socialist Fabian Society. The magazine has; according to its present self-description; a left-of-centre political position. By USA standards this source is considered left biased based on story selection and wording. They are always well sourced and factual. (5/13/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "http://nymag.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Established in 1968. New York is a bi-weekly magazine concerned with life; culture; politics; and style generally; and with a particular emphasis on New York City. NY Mag has a left wing bias in story selection and reporting; but is always sourced and factual. (5/13/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "http://observer.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Observer (OB) is an online publication primarily serving New York city. This review centers specifically on OBs National and International reporting."),
new Bias(source: "http://www.newyorker.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "The New Yorker is an American magazine of reportage; commentary; criticism; essays; fiction; satire; cartoons; and poetry. It is published by Cond Nast. Started as a weekly in 1925; the magazine is now published 47 times annually; with five of these issues covering two-week spans. The New York is trustworthy for factual accuracy; but with a left wing bias in wording and report choices. (5/13/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "http://newscorpse.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "News Corpses mission is to expose corporate media. They embrace independent media; but with a left wing bias in reporting and wording. For example; there is significant use of loaded words in headlines; such as: Trump Whines Because Democrats Are Smiling  No; Theyre Laughing at You; Loser. Due to a very strong bias it is recommended to fact check this source. This is a borderline questionable source. (10/14/2016) Updated (3/29/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.newshounds.us/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "A website dedicated to exposing Fox News in lies and misreporting. Has a left wing bias and sometimes takes information out of context."),
new Bias(source: "http://www.newslogue.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Newslogue is highly biased towards liberal and progressive views. The articles are worded and weighted very heavily towards the left and read more like op-eds instead of news articles. The articles are penned primarily by Caitlin Johnson; and the site appears more like a personal blog than a news site. As such; the articles arent always entirely factual either. Example; in their article The Right Has No Answer For Automation Job Loss; But The Left Does the author maintains that the right is against a Universal Basic Income. Even a simple search reveals that there is indeed bipartisan support for it. (D. Kelley)"),
new Bias(source: "https://nowthisnews.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "NowThis News was founded by Huffington Post co-founder and former chairman Kenneth Lerer and former Huffington Post CEO Eric Hippeau. Uses Facebook; Snapchat; Twitter; Instagram; Vine; Tumblr; and YouTube as primary outlets. Political news reports have a strong liberal/progressive leaning bias; heavily relying on meme culture and soundbites; often omitting certain key facts spoken in videos clips."),
new Bias(source: "https://www.opednews.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "OpEdNews is an open progressive forum for opinion and news. Because each individual author is wholly responsible for the content she or he submits; veracity varies with the individual writer and its entirely up to readers to assess journalistic quality and bias. There is no firewall between biased opinion and well-sourced analytical reporting. Volunteer editors moderate the posts for bad taste and seek to discourage libelous and slanderous content. Posts the editors like get headlined on the front page. Frequent contributors may earn the trust of the publisher and bypass editor pre-screening to post directly. Spirited and thought-provoking discussions often follow articles as comments. (R. Shreve)"),
new Bias(source: "https://www.pastemagazine.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Paste is a monthly music and entertainment digital magazine published in the United States by Wolfgangs Vault. Its tagline is Signs of Life in Music; Film and Culture.It ran as a print publication from 2002 to 2010 before converting to online-only. While Paste Magazine is primarily a Music and entertainment magazine it does have a political section with typical left wing bias. It utilizes strong loaded words that are pro-liberal and anti-conservative. The source is factual in reporting on political news; but has a left wing editorial position."),
new Bias(source: "http://people.com/politics/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "People is an American weekly magazine of celebrity and human-interest stories; published by Time Inc. With a readership of 46.6 million adults; People has the largest audience of any American magazine. The online version of People Magazine has a politics section that has a moderate left wing bias through wording and story selection."),
new Bias(source: "https://photographyisnotacrime.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Photography is Not a Crime; abbreviated to PINAC and published under the trade names PINAC News; is an organization and news website that focuses on rights of civilians who photograph and film police misconduct and other similar activities in the United States incorporated in June 2014 as PINAC Inc. a Florida not for profit corporation. It was founded in 2007 following the arrest of its creator; Carlos Miller; a veteran news reporter and photojournalist.PINAC focuses on First Amendment issues that intersect with governmental oppression of those rights; normally by police officers. It also gives civilians tips on how to interact with the police and assert their constitutionally protected rights. This source uses loaded words in their headlines; but they source their information well. (11/29/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.pinknews.co.uk/home/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Pink News is a UK-based online newspaper marketed to the lesbian; gay; bisexual and transgender community (LGBT). They have a left wing opinionbias; however their reporting is strong and mostly evidence based. (11/12/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "http://politicalupdater.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Political Updater is a news and opinion website that reports with loaded words and not always well sourced information. While the site does seem to report both left and right stories there ismore that favor the left in our sampling. (8/15/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.politicususa.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "PoliticusUsa is a left wing biased news and opinion website. PoliticusUsa typically sources to credible media sourcessuch as Reutersandare factual in reporting as we were unable to find any instances of failed fact checks. Though headlines tend to be somewhat sensational; the content of articles is evidence based with occasional use of loaded words that convey emotion. In short; PoliticusUsa is left biased through story choicesand wording; but factual in reporting. (5/15/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.pravdareport.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Pravda Reports is a far left communist newspaper from Russia. It does not always report accurately about USA and other international news. (7/30/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "https://www.pressprogress.ca/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Press Progress; an online news and analysis website; is a project of the Broadbent Institute which seeks to provide an online Progressive Political news source. Press Progress has a left bias in reporting stories and uses moderately loaded word choices. They do however; link to mostly credible sources. (2/18/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://proudemocrat.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "I am pretty sure you have gathered the bias by the name alone. There is a very strong left wing bias here. They occasionally produce good content; butthey also fail to source sometimes to quality sources."),
new Bias(source: "http://rabble.ca/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Rabble.ca is an non-profit alternative Canadian online magazine founded in 2001.Rabble.ca works in partnership with the Canadian Centre for Policy Alternatives and the Centre for Social Justice. It features podcasts; videos and an discussion board called babble. Rabble uses a lot of loaded language in the headlines; and within the articles. Mostly in commentaries they describe themselves as blurring the line between readers and contributors; providing a space for issues exploring political passions and an opportunity to expand ideas. They are an openly progressive site; reporting and commenting on current news with a clear left bias. (F. Locke Siewert 2/11/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.rappler.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Rappler is an online news site based in the Philippines with a bureau in Jakarta; Indonesia.One of the distinguishing features of Rappler is its Mood Meter consisting of bubbles showing the way people react to certain news.The Mood Meter is embedded on each story. Users are asked how does this story make you feel? and are given 8 different emotions to choose from  happy; sad; angry; afraid; annoyed; inspired; amused and dont care. The top ten stories with the most votes over a 48-hour period appear on the Mood Navigator. Rappler has left wing bias in reporting news from the Philippines. They are fiercely opposed to President Duterte and his anti-drug campaign where he advocates killingdrug users. We give a mixed factual reporting rating based on some disputes regarding claims made by Rappler. When reporting international news Rappler is relatively low biased and straightforward. (5/16/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.rawprogressive.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Raw Progressiveis a news and opinion website with a borderline extreme left bias in reporting. Virtually every headline utilizes sensational loaded words that induce clicking (Clickbait). The content of articles; are typically sourced to far left sources such as LeftScoop. Raw Progressive typically takes a news story and interjects left biased opinions around the story.The opinion is always pro-left and anti-right. Although we could notfind any instances of failed fact checks; we still rate them mixed for factual reporting based on strong opinions that can be distracting and misleading from the facts. This source also does not have an About page or any other author information; which reduces credibility."),
new Bias(source: "http://www.rawstory.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "The Raw Story is an American online news organization founded in 2004 by John Byrne. It covers current national and international political and economic news and publishes its own editorials and investigative pieces. The Raw Story describes itself as progressive; bringing attention to stories that it sees as downplayed or ignored by other media outlets. Raw Story demonstrates left wing bias in reporting and story selection.Raw Story has a Half-True claim with Politifact and an Unproven claim with Snopes. (5/15/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.redpepper.org.uk/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Red Pepper is an independent radical red and green magazine based in the UK. Has strong socialist biases; but is well sourced."),
new Bias(source: "https://rewire.news/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Rewire is a website focused on reproductive and sexual health from a pro-reproductive rights perspective.The website began as a UN Foundation blog in 2006; and became its own nonprofit organization in January 2012. Although the site has a left wing political perspective it does offer mostly evidence based information. (10/17/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "http://revcom.us/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Revcom.us is the voice of the Revolutionary Communist Party of the USA. With that said is has a strong Communist bias. It uses strong loaded words to describe other political parties. The sole purpose of the site is to promote Communism."),
new Bias(source: "http://revolution-news.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Revolution News is a news and opinion website featuring independent journalists. Published stories typically have a moderate left wing bias and are usually sourced properly."),
new Bias(source: "http://www.rightwingwatch.org/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Right Wing Watch keeps track of a variety of organizations; but the groups they track do tend to be conservative extremist in one regard or another. This source does occasionally take statements out of context. Needs to be fact checked. (5/15/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "https://trofire.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Ring of Fire is a nationally syndicated American talk radio program that has Overt left wing bias. Each host has their own style and level of bias; but most source reliable sources in their reporting. They do however; take many things out of context."),
new Bias(source: "http://www.salon.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Salon is a progressive/liberal website created by David Talbot in 1995 and part of Salon Media Group. It focuses on U.S. politics and current affairs. Salon hashas left wing bias through reporting and wording; but can be trusted to source to mostly credible information. (5/15/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.scarymommy.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Scary Mommy is a news and opinion website/blog that is geared toward parenting. They also cover news and politics with a left wing bias in reporting choices. There is minimal use of loaded words and all stories are factual and/or sourced properly."),
new Bias(source: "http://shareblue.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Shareblue is an online political news source. It is affiliated with Blue Nation Review and David Brock. This source; like Blue Nation Review has a strongleft wing bias in story selection and wording. Shareblue also occasionally publishes stories that are propagandist and misleading factually."),
new Bias(source: "http://www.slate.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Slate is an English-language online current affairs; politics and culture magazine in the United States that trends towards a liberalviewpoint through story choices and wording. Slate tends to source to credible information; but uses rather sensationalized headlines to increase clicks. (5/15/2016) Updated (2/24/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.worldsocialism.org/spgb/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Socialist Standard is a monthly socialist magazine published without interruption since September 1904 by the Socialist Party of Great Britain. The magazine is written in a simple; direct style and focuses mainly on socialist advocacy and Marxian analysis of current events; particularly those affecting the United Kingdom."),
new Bias(source: "http://www.sourcewatch.org/index.php/SourceWatch", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "SourceWatchaims to produce a directory of public relations firms; think tanks; industry-funded organizations and industry-friendly experts that work to influence public opinion and public policy on behalf ofcorporations; governments and special interest groups (Wikipedia). SourceWatchs reporting always tends to favor liberals. They do however; source their content and are considered factual."),
new Bias(source: "https://www.stpete4peace.org/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Chris Ernesto (born October 16; 1963) is a founding member of St. Pete for Peace;a non-partisan antiwar organization providing peace oriented education events and services to the Tampa Bay; FL community since 2003. He created and manages the StPeteForPeace.org; OccupyArrests.comand USinAfrica.comwebsites. Ernesto has also organized numerous demonstrations; published multiple articles and videos; and is a lead researcher for St. Pete for Peace where he has developed dozens of fact sheets. St. Pete for Peace has a left wing political bias; however; they do source well; although at times to other left wing sources. Otherwise; this is a pretty trustworthy source for anti-war information."),
new Bias(source: "http://talkingpointsmemo.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Talking Points Memo (or TPM) is a liberal web-based political journalism website created and run by Josh Marshall; a journalist; liberal bloggerand historian.It debuted on November 12; 2000.TPM has liberal bias in story selection andproduces some very credible journalism. They almost always source to credible information. (7/26/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.takepart.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "TakePart produces a Web site with a daily cycle of original articles; blogs; and videos on the culture and lifestyle of change. Topics of coverage include animals; arts; food; education; the environment; green tech; politics; culture; health and innovation."),
new Bias(source: "http://www.telesurtv.net/english/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "La Nueva Televisora del Sur (teleSUR; English: The New Television Station of the South) is multi-state funded; panLatin American terrestrial and satellite television network sponsored by the governments of Venezuela; Cuba; Ecuador; Nicaragua; Uruguay; and Bolivia that is headquartered in Caracas; Venezuela. TeleSUR has been accused of being a propaganda tool forHugo Chavez and his successors. TeleSUR uses minimal loaded words; but has a very strong pro-Venezuela and anti-American bias in reporting. (1/5/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://prospect.org/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "The American Prospect is a quarterly American political magazine dedicated to American liberalism. Based in Washington; D.C.; The American Prospect says it aims to advance liberal and progressive goals through reporting; analysis; and debate about todays realities and tomorrows possibilities. The American Prospecthas a left wing bias in story selection and is always well sourced. (5/15/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.blue-route.org/blog/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "The Blue Route is a news and opinion website with strong left wing bias in reporting and emotional word use. They sometimes source to other far left sources and many articles are opinion based; hence we give a mixed factual rating. (7/26/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.thecanary.co/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "The Canary is a left-wing political blog in the United Kingdom. The Canary uses strong loaded words with a left-wing bias. They are evidence based and provide sources for claims. They typically report only one side of the story and have a strong liberal political affiliation. (12/1/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "https://www.climaterealityproject.org/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "The Climate Reality Project; founded by Al Goreis a non-profit organization involved in education and advocacy related to climate change. The mission of the Climate Reality Project is to focus on climate change education and countering climate change denial campaigns worldwide. While TCRP is well sourced and factual in scientific information; it also has a left wing bias in its criticism of President Trump and Conservatives.We give this organization a moderate left bias rating based on story selection that opposes the conservative point of viewthat climate change is not human caused or simply not important. (3/23/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://thedailybanter.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "The Daily Banter is an online news and opinion site. It produces well written articles that must be filtered through their liberal bias on most stories. Most information is sourced."),
new Bias(source: "http://the-daily.buzz/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "The Daily Buzz is a multimedia and news website that covers a variety of topics; including politics. The Daily Buzz features many humorous articles; but they also present straightforward news that is well sourced and factual. News reporting tends to have a left bias in story selection and somewhat sensationalized headlines. However; the content of these news articles are often well writtenand always link to credible sources."),
new Bias(source: "https://www.thedailyvox.co.za/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "The Daily Vox is a South African news and opinion website. They present news with slightly loaded words that have a left wing bias. Most articles are well sourced. (1/22/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.democratichub.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "This is perhaps the easiest review ever done. From The Democratic Hubs about page: Our online community is for liberals; progressives; moderates; independent and anyone who has a favorable opinion of Democrats and/or liberal political views or is critical of Republican ideology. That really about sums it up. This source uses strong loaded words that favor Democrats and discredits Republicans. All content is written by member bloggers and is highly opinionated; which matches their appropriate description. At least they are honest in who they are."),
new Bias(source: "http://www.thefrisky.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "The Frisky is a womens entertainment and lifestyle website which was launched in 2008. When covering political news they have a left wing bias with loaded words and story selection. Though biased they do source to credible information."),
new Bias(source: "http://thegrio.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "TheGrio is an American website with news; opinion; entertainment and video content geared toward African Americans.TheGrio is one of the largest news sources for black America. Originally launched in June 2009 as a division of NBC News;it became a division of MSNBC in 2013. Covers a lot of entertainment news; but also does cover politics with a left wing bias and typically sources properly."),
new Bias(source: "https://theintellectualist.co/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "The Intellectualist is a news aggregation website that primarily usesleft-center sources. Most sources are credible; however we rate the Intellectualist left biased because almost all stories are favorable to the left or damaging to the right. The Intellectualist is factual in sourcing; but biased based on story choices. (3/9/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.themilitant.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "The Militant is an international Socialist newsweekly connected to the Socialist Workers Party (SWP) and the Pathfinder Press.It is published in the United States and distributed in other countries such as Canada; the United Kingdom; Australia; France; Sweden; Iceland; and New Zealand. Has a left wing socialist bias in reporting; but does not use loaded words and sources well."),
new Bias(source: "http://www.morningstaronline.co.uk/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Morning Star is a left-wing British daily tabloid newspaper with a focus on social; political and trade union issues. Articles and comment columns are contributed by writers from socialist; communist; social democratic; green and religious perspectives. Uses strong words with a liberal bias and has sensational headlines. Mostly links to credible sources. (5/15/2016) Updated (4/26/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "https://www.thenation.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "The Nation is the oldest continuously published weekly magazine in the United States; and the most widely read weekly journal of progressive political and cultural news; opinion and analysis. Founded in 1865; The Nation produces well written journalism that is factual and well sourced. They demonstrate left wing bias in story choices and wording. (5/15/2016) Updated (4/26/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.nationalmemo.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "The National Memo is an American online news site and newsletter. Founded in 2011 by award-winning journalist and editor Joe Conason; features daily breaking news and commentary as well as analysis from Americas top progressive thinkers.With a focus on American politics; The National Memo also covers world news and events; consumer finance; health; travel and entertainment. The National Memo is always well sourced and factual; but the bias clearly favors the left in almost every story. This is a solid source for credible information; but on a whole this source does not always cover both sides of the story."),
new Bias(source: "http://www.thenewcivilrightsmovement.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "The New Civil Rights Movement is a website news source that promotes civil rights for LGBT people. They use strong left biased language regarding conservatives and have an unproven claim from Snopes."),
new Bias(source: "http://other98.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "The Other 98% is a non-profit activist group that are tired of corporate control of our government; our institutions; and our planet. Their primary mission is to get money out of politics and reduce corporate influence. They present information with a left wing bias regarding reporting and wording. They also have a mixed file from Politifact."),
new Bias(source: "http://www.progressive.org/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "The Progressive is an American monthly magazine of politics; culture and progressivism with a pronounced liberal perspective. Founded in 1909 by Senator Robert Fighting Bob La Follette; it was originally called La Follettes Weekly and then simply La Follettes.In 1929; it was recapitalized and had its name changed to The Progressive (Wikipedia). The Progressive has a left wing bias in story selection. They source all stories to credible information."),
new Bias(source: "http://www.theroot.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "The Root is an English-language American online magazine of African-American culture launched on January 28; 2008; by Henry Louis Gates; Jr. and Donald E. Graham; and was owned by Graham Holdings Company (Wikipedia). Solid evidence based reporting with a left wing bias in wording and political affiliation."),
new Bias(source: "http://www.villagevoice.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "The Village Voice was created in 1955 as a platform for the creative community. As the nations first alternative newsweekly; The Village Voice introduced free-form; high-spirited; and passionate journalism into the public discourse. The recipient of three Pulitzer Prizes; the National Press Foundation Award and the George Polk Award; The Village Voice remains a go-to source for coverage of New Yorks politics and vast cultural landscape. The Village Voice produces high quality journalism and sources political information well. It does however have a left wing bias in what it reports and the use of emotional (loaded) words."),
new Bias(source: "https://thewalrus.ca/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "The Walrus is a Canadian general interest magazine which publishes long-form journalism on Canadian and international affairs; along with fiction and poetry by Canadian writers . The Walrus produces high quality liberal journalism that is factually sourced."),
new Bias(source: "http://thinkprogress.org/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "ThinkProgress is an American political news blog. It is a project of the Center for American Progress; a progressive public policy research and advocacy organization. Has a left wing bias in story selection and has failed some fact checks including these from Snopes. (5/15/2016) Updated (2/24/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "https://this.org/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "This Magazine is an independent alternative Canadian political magazine. Has a left wing bias in story selection and is usually factually sourced."),
new Bias(source: "http://www.towleroad.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Towleroad is blog founded by Andy Towleand isbased in New York City. Towle; who is gay; started his blog Towleroad in 2003.The blog focuses on gays; pop culture; photography; politics; media; entertainment; technology; and travel. Towleroad uses strong loaded language with a far left bias in reporting. Most articles are sourced reasonable well; but their is significant opinion interjected into each article."),
new Bias(source: "http://www.tribunemagazine.org/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Tribune is a democratic socialist fortnightly newspaper; founded in 1937 and published in London. It has always been independent but has usually supported the Labour Party from the left. Has a left wing political bias; but is well sourced to credible information."),
new Bias(source: "http://www.truthdig.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Truthdig is a news website that provides a mix of long-form articles; interviews; and blog-like commentary on current events; delivered from a politically progressivepoint of view. Truthdig has a left wing bias in what they choose to report and the words they use; but the articles are generally well written and reasonably sourced. (11/18/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.truth-out.org/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Truthout is a 501(c)(3) nonprofit; progressive news organization in the United States that operates a web site and distributes a daily newsletter. Registered in September 2001; in Sacramento; California; Truthout publishes original political news articles; opinion pieces; video reports and artwork. According to its web site; Truthout works to broaden and diversify the political discussion by introducing independent voices and focusing on under covered issues and unconventional thinking. Truthout has a strong left wing bias in reporting choices and wording. They also have reported some stories that were not factual. For example; a reporter claimed that Karl Rove was indicted on charges when in fact he wasnt. The reporter continued to make the claim without evidence. See link here. Although this is only one example it shows that this source should be checked when in doubt. (5/15/2016) Updated (4/26/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://uproxx.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Uproxx is an American digital media company that covers entertainment and culture. It was founded in 2008 by Jarret Myer and Brian Brater and acquired by Woven Digital in 2014. The sites target audience is males aged 18-34. Uproxx has a left wing political affiliation in reporting. They are generally factual and source to credible information. (10/3/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "https://www.upworthy.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Upworthy is a website for viral content started in March 2012 by Eli Pariser; the former executive director of MoveOn; and Peter Koechley; the former managing editor of The Onion.It uses virality to promote stories with a progressive bent on political and social issues. Upworthy claims to fact check every post; we couldnt find anything to dispute this. They do however have a left wing bias in story selection. (5/15/2016) Updated (6/2/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://theuspoliticalpost.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "US Politcal Post is a News and Opinion blog with left wing bias in reporting. As of 12/22/16 this source does not appear to be active any longer."),
new Bias(source: "http://usuncut.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "US Uncut has overt left wing bias in story selection and wording. Does not have an about or mission page to explain its positions. Does not provide biographies for its writers. Not all articles are well sourced and are highly sensationalized. Requires fact checking against reliable sources. (5/15/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.vanityfair.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Vanity Fair is a magazine of popular culture; fashion; and current affairs published by Cond Nast (Wikipedia). Vanity Fair also publishes political content that has a moderate left wing bias. This is seen in several articles critical of conservatives and positive in favor of more liberal politicians. Overall; Vanity Fair is well written and mostly factual; but there is a clear left wing bias."),
new Bias(source: "http://vote.us.org/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Vote is a news and opinion blog with a left wing bias in reporting. Most articles favor liberals and oppose conservatives. There is some use of loaded words; which is to be expected from a mostly opinion based website. Due to this source writing mostly opinion pieces we rate it mixed for factual reporting as sourcing is limited. (6/3/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.vox.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Vox is an American advocacy news website run by Vox Media; co-founded by liberal columnists Ezra Klein; Melissa Bell; and Matt Yglesias and launched in April 2014. Vox presents with left wing bias in reporting and story choices. There is some use of loaded words; but most articles are sourced to credible information. (5/15/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "http://washingtonmonthly.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Washington Monthly is a bimonthly nonprofit magazine of United States politics and government that is based in Washington; D.C.Has a liberal bias in reporting and word choices."),
new Bias(source: "http://wonkette.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Wonkette is a news and opinion website with a very strong liberal bias. They sometimes post tongue in cheek articles that can be misleading. Overall; they source their information and will correct factual errors when they occur. Although they are very biased in their wording and content they are reliable for information. (5/15/2016) Updated (3/10/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "https://tytnetwork.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "The Young Turks (TYT) is an American political commentary web series that was created by journalist Cenk Uygur; Ben Mankiewicz and Dave Koller. Currently co-hosted by Uygur and Ana Kasparian; its stance isprogressive/left-wing; although its primary focus is on political commentary; the program provides opinion on topics of varying news genres. Although very left biased in delivery the Young Turks do a decentjob of sourcing their information with credibility."),
new Bias(source: "https://zcomm.org/zmag/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left Bias", notes: "Z Magazine was established in 1987.It is published in print and on-line. Contributors to the magazine include Noam Chomsky;Edward S. Herman;Mike Kuhlenbeck;Jack Rasmas;Paul Streetand Kevin Zeese. Has a distinct Libertarian-Socialist-Anarchist Bias."),
new Bias(source: "http://abcnews.go.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left-Center Bias", notes: "ABC News is the news division of the American Broadcasting Company (ABC); owned by the Disney Media Networks division of The Walt Disney Company. Like most so called Mainstream media sources ABC has been accused of liberal bias. In reality; ABC is mostly trustworthy with a left of center bias. (5/15/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "http://abovethelaw.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left-Center Bias", notes: "Above the Law (often abbreviated ATL) is a news website about law; law schools; and the legal profession.Established in 2006; the site is owned and published by Breaking Media. Uses minimal loaded words; is sourced and factual in reporting. Story selection has a left-center bias. (1/31/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "https://aeon.co/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left-Center Bias", notes: "Aeon is a digital magazine of ideas and culture. Publishing new articles every weekday; Aeon describes itself as a publication which asks the biggest questions and finds the freshest; most original answers; provided by world-leading authorities on science; philosophy and society. They also covers news and politics with a slight left-center bias in reporting choices; is factually sourced and uses minimal emotional wording. (D. Van Zandt 2/18/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.aljazeera.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left-Center Bias", notes: "Al Jazeera is a Doha-based state-funded broadcaster owned by the Al Jazeera Media Network; which is partly funded by the House of Thani; the ruling family of Qatar.Initially launched as an Arabic news and current affairs satellite TV channel; Al Jazeera has since expanded into a network with several outlets; including the Internet and specialty TV channels in multiple languages. Al Jazeera is among the largest news organizations with 80 bureaus around the world. Al Jazeera is owned by the government of Qatar and has pro-Qatari bias. However; Al Jazeera uses low bias whenreporting USA news and often sources to credible information. (5/15/2016) Updated (6/25/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.al-monitor.com/pulse/home.html", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left-Center Bias", notes: "Al-Monitor is a media site launched in February 2012 by the Arab American entrepreneur Jamal Danieland based in Washington; DC. Al-Monitor provides reporting and analysis from and about the Middle East through both original and translated content. Al Monitor is well sourced; credible and factual. Has a left of center bias politically. (5/15/2016) Updated (6/25/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "https://www.guttmacher.org/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left-Center Bias", notes: "Is a leading research and policy organization committed to advancing sexual and reproductive health and rights in the United States. Left of Center politically; but excellent sourcing and factual information. (5/15/2016) Updated (1/12/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.adn.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left-Center Bias", notes: "The Alaska Dispatch News is a daily newspaper published by the Alaska Dispatch; and based in Anchorage; Alaska.The newspaper has won the Pulitzer Prize twice in the Public Service category; in 1976 and 1989.The Alaska Dispatch News is factual in reporting and has a left-center editorial bias. (8/12/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.timesunion.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left-Center Bias", notes: "The AlbanyTimes Union is an American daily newspaper; serving the Capital Region of New York; United States. Although the newspaper focuses on Albany and its suburbs; it covers all parts of the four-county area; including the cities of Troy; Schenectady and Saratoga Springs. (10/6/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.ohio.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left-Center Bias", notes: "The Akron Beacon Journal is a morning newspaper in Ohio; United States; and published by Black Press. It is the sole daily newspaper in Akron and is distributed throughout Northeast Ohio. The paper places a strong emphasis on local news and business. (10/7/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.amny.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left-Center Bias", notes: "AM New York is a morning free daily newspaper that is published in New York City by Newsday. AM New York has a left center reporting bias; but is well sourced and factual in reporting. (3/16/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.americamagazine.org/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left-Center Bias", notes: "America is a national weekly magazine published by the Jesuits of the United States and headquartered in midtown Manhattan. It contains news and opinion about Roman Catholicism and how it relates to American politics and cultural life. Published continuously since 1909; it is one of the oldest periodicals in the U.S. America is well sourced and factual. They use minimal loaded words in headlines and articles. While they do take somewhat conservative Catholic positions from an editorial standpoint; their reporting of news has a slight left center bias through favoring more liberal causes such as income equality and environmental protection. This is a reliable source. (D. Van Zandt 4/13/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "https://www.aclu.org/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left-Center Bias", notes: "The American Civil Liberties Union (ACLU) is a nonpartisan; non-profit; organization whose stated mission is to defend and preserve the individual rights and liberties guaranteed to every person in this country by the Constitution and laws of the United States.It works through litigation; lobbying; and community empowerment. The ACLU in their blog section and even news section often cite to places like the Huffington Post for news articles but sometimes they will usebasic reporting like AP or Reuters. Beyond their news and blog posts most of the site covers issues that are often considered more liberal causes but most often it is consistent with theirstance on the rights they champion. TheACLU has defended the KKK; Pro Abortion; and Neo-Nazis right to assemble and protest (1 2 3). They will often be accused of being left biased as they do not advocate for gun rights; however they equally do not champion gun regulations either. A quick search for Gun Rights or even Guns will yield no results or results only related to search and seizure cases they have taken on. They do not agree on the individuals rights to own firearms but do not advocate on their beliefs. They have teamed up with the NRA several times in a sort of odd fellowship (4). Their Blog & News feeds can often be filled with more left leaning stances; but they are not biased in their case work load or defending the rights they advocate for. There have been times Justice Scalia the most outspoken and most conservative justice at the time had ideas that line up with the ACLU (5). Most modern conservatives may often take issue with much of what the ACLU advocates and litigates in courts. However; the ACLU has defended religious freedoms in the school as well. Including the right to pray in school (6). I would try to advocate that the ACLU is more neutral than left; but with the major shift in American politics to the right; I can no longer advocate that stance. (M. Allen 2/9/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://ahtribune.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left-Center Bias", notes: "The American Herald Tribune is an online independent news source. The American Herald Tribune produces quality journalism that is factually based. Has a left-center bias in content and reporting. (11/26/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.adl.org/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left-Center Bias", notes: "The Anti-Defamation League is an international Jewish non-governmental organization based in the United States. Describing itself as the nations premier civil rights/human relations agency; the ADL states that it fights anti-Semitism and all forms of bigotry; defends democratic ideals and protects civil rights for all; doing so through information; education; legislation; and advocacy. Has been accused of having a liberal political bias. (10/6/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "https://www.aol.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left-Center Bias", notes: "AOL is an online magazine featuring a variety of content; from politics to lifestyle to video games. While they dont carry a lot of political content; what they do carry is factual; well sourced and delivered with minimal bias. Despite a very slight left slant it is still well within the Least Biased category. (D. Kelley 3/3/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://aranews.net/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left-Center Bias", notes: "ARA News is a Syrian independent press agency concerned with covering local developments across Syria; including its Kurdish region. (8/30/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "http://tucson.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left-Center Bias", notes: "The Arizona Daily Star is the major morning daily newspaper that serves Tucson and surrounding districts of southern Arizona in the United States. They report news factually and with sources. Has a left-center editorial bias. (7/30/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.citizen-times.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left-Center Bias", notes: "The Asheville Citizen-Times is a major daily newspaper from Asheville; North Carolina. Is well sourced with just a slight left of center bias in news coverage. (10/7/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.ajc.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left-Center Bias", notes: "The Atlanta Journal-Constitution (AJC) is the only major daily newspaper in the metropolitan area of Atlanta; Georgia; United States. The AJC is factual and sourced in reporting with a left of center editorial stance. (5/15/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "https://www.theatlantic.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left-Center Bias", notes: "The Atlantic is an American magazine; founded in 1857 as The Atlantic Monthly in Boston; Massachusetts. Since 2006; the magazine is based in Washington; D.C.Created as a literary and cultural commentary magazine; it has grown to achieve a national reputation as a high-quality review organ with a moderate worldview.The periodical has won more National Magazine Awards than any other monthly magazine. Has a slightly liberal bias in reporting coverage; put produces exceptional journalism that is sourced and factual. (5/15/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.atlanticmedia.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left-Center Bias", notes: "Atlantic Media owns the following sources:www.govexec.com; www.nextgov.com; www.routefifty.com; qz.com; www.nationaljournal.com; www.theatlantic.com; www.citylab.com; www.defenseone.com. They borrow writers and share stories depending on the contact they are going with. For example; an article on www.defenseone.com uses an article from www.nextgov.com the writer is Joseph Marks  who covers cybersecurity for Nextgov. He previously covered cybersecurity for Politico.The sites all seem to have particular themes they focus on. Government; military; cyber; city; etc. Atlantic Media is the main company and keeps all these brands under that umbrella sharing writers and sources. Overall they are well sourced; truth filled; andlean slightly left. (M. Allen 5/13/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.attn.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left-Center Bias", notes: "ATTN is a political and social site geared towards millennials; although not exclusively so. Founded by Matthew Segal; a political activist and commentator who writes for the Huffington Post and is also a frequent commentator on MSNBC. While Mr. Segals politics are unashamedly left leaning; the content of ATTN is factual and well sourced. The political tone of the articles is mixed; running from Left Bias to Least Biased. While this reflects the individual authors opinions more than any specific editorial stance this slight lack of focus in overall content is what prevented ATTN from receiving a Least Biased rating. Additionally; ATTN does cite itself occasionally in its other articles; which I find a bit self serving when any news site does it. Even if the content cited is factual. While again; this may reflect the individual authors rather than editorial intent; its easy enough to use external sources instead. That said; the quality of the content on the site is very high; and except for a slight caveat on the bias and self sourcing; I wouldnt hesitate to recommend ATTN to anyone looking for a solid news source. (D. Kelley 2/28/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "https://www.axios.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left-Center Bias", notes: "AXIOS Media or Axios is a news and information company started in 2016 by Politico co-founder Jim VandeHei; former Chief White House correspondent at Politico; Mike Allen; and former Politico Chief Revenue Officer Roy Schwartz. Axios is well sourced and factual. Has a left-Center political bias in story selection. (2/1/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "https://backchannel.com/", factuality: "VERY HIGH", biasType: "Left-Center Bias", notes: "Back Channel (BC) is a technology reporting site that reports primarily on the internet and social media. The articles on the site are factual and well sourced. What political news BC carries is tech-centric as well; such as the article concerning Ajit Pai; President Trumps pick to head the FCC. While the reporting on BC is solid there is; however; a slightly left bias in the overall tone. Much of that bias is inherent in the subject matter; but it doesnt account for all of it. For this reason Back Channel is rated Left Center. (D. Kelley 3/14/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.baltimoresun.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left-Center Bias", notes: "The Baltimore Sun is the largest general-circulation daily newspaper based in the American state of Maryland and provides coverage of local and regional news; events; issues; people; and industries. Founded in 1837; it is owned by Tronc; Inc. The Baltimore Sun is well sourced and factual with a left wing editorial bias. (7/29/2016) Updated (6/26/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "https://baptistnews.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left-Center Bias", notes: "Baptist News Global is an independent Baptist news agency. It was founded in 2014 as a merger of Associated Baptist Press (ABP); which was founded in 1990;and the Religious Herald; which was founded in 1828. Baptist News Global publishes curated news from many least biased; left-center and left wing sources. They also publish their own news that has minimal bias. Politically this source aligns in the left-center. Information is well sourced and trustworthy. (8/23/2016) Updated (6/26/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.bbc.com/news", factuality: "VERY HIGH", biasType: "Left-Center Bias", notes: "The British Broadcasting Corporation (BBC) is a British public service broadcaster. It is headquartered at Broadcasting House in London; and is the worlds oldest national broadcasting organisationand the largest broadcaster in the world by number of employees. The BBC is an outstanding journalistic source. They have just a slight left of center political bias in reporting coverage and they are always impeccably sourced. (5/15/2016) Updated (6/26/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.bjreview.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left-Center Bias", notes: "Founded in March 1958as the weekly Peking Review; it was an important tool for the Peoples Republic of Chinagovernment to communicate to the rest of world.Has a Communist; Maoist perspective; but reports new factually. (8/16/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.berkshireeagle.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Left-Center Bias", notes: "The Berkshire Eagle is an American daily newspaper published in Pittsfield; Massachusetts; and covering all of Berkshire County; as well as four New York communities near Pittsfield. It is considered a newspaper of record for Berkshire County; Massachusetts. Factual with a Left-Center editorial bias. (10/7/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "http://billmoyers.com/", factuality: "VERY HIGH", biasType: "Left-Center Bias", notes: "Bill Moyers is a retired American news reporter and journalist. In 2012 Bill Moyers launched the website BillMoyers.com thatcombines a blog featuring essays and videos by managing editor Bill Moyers; as well as the perspectives of other journalists; scholars; activists; and creative men and women in the arts and sciences. The site also includes a video archive of Bill Moyerss 40-plus year journalism career; offering nearly 1;000 archived programs; video clips and online-original segments (Billmoyers.com). Moyers has won countless journalism awards throughout his career and the content on his website is no exception to those standards. All articles are well sourced and factual. The content does have a left-center lean based on story selection and wording. (D. Van Zandt 2/25/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://us.blastingnews.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Left-Center Bias", notes: "BlastingNews is a very content heavy news and opinion website. The website boasts 250;000 citizen writers and 11 million readers. Due to there being so much content on a wide array of topics it is difficult to fully gauge the bias of this website. In reviewing articles it appears there is an anti-Trump bias and articles that tend to favor more liberal causes. However; due to there being so many writers from diverse backgrounds this is not always the case. We give a mixed factual rating based on other sources claiming this is a questionable source. Our confidence level on this review is medium. (6/24/2017)"),
