new Bias(source: "http://dailysurge.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "The Daily Surge is a news and opinion website with a right wing bias in reporting. Many headlines and articles utilize loaded words to convey positive or negative emotion. Daily Surge routinely publishes articles against the left and for the right. Most articles are sourced properly to credible information; however many are sourced to other far right wing websites. Daily Surge is also on Politifacts fake news list. This site is sometimes misleading; but it is not fake news. (5/23/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.dcstatesman.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "The DC Statesman is a news and opinion website with a very strong right wing bias. They utilize loaded headlines and do not always source their information to other credible sources. For example they quote known purveyor of fake news Mike Cernovich for articles such as this:http://www.dcstatesman.com/report-susan-rice-ordered-unmasking-trump-officials/.(12/15/2016) Updated (4/5/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://debatepost.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "The Debate Post is a Canadian news and opinion website. The Debate posts has moderate right wing bias in story selection; but uses minimal loaded words and tends to source to mostly credible sources; howeverthere are a few articles that source to far right sources such as Breitbart. (2/17/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://disobedientmedia.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "Disobedient Media is a news and opinion website with a right wing bias in story selection and reporting. Disobedient Media uses moderate loaded words and tends to source well to credible information. Occasionally they will source to some pretty far right sources. (2/16/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.drudgereport.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "The Drudge Report is a politically conservative American news aggregation website run by Matt Drudge.The site consists mainly of links to stories from the United States and international mainstream media about politics; entertainment; and current events; it also has links to many columnists. Occasionally; Drudge authors new stories himself; based on tips. The Drudge Report focuses on sensationalized stories with a right wing bias. They have a poor record with fact checkers. (7/19/2016) Updated (4/5/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://factsandlogic.org/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "Facts and Logic About the Middle East (FLAME) is a non-profit pro-Israel organization based in San Francisco; California.Its stated purpose is the research and publication of the facts regarding developments in the Middle East and exposing false propaganda that might harm the interests of the United States and its allies in that area of the world. The source has an extreme bias for Israel and against Muslims.According to theThe Village Voice; when a reporter pointed out the overt bigotry in a FLAME ad in 1998 that described Islam as virulent and blamed it for promoting violence against the U.S. and Israel; FLAMEs Gerardo Joffe said All Arab Muslims may not be a bunch of fanatics; but Ive never met one who isnt. (1/11/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.familysecuritymatters.org/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "Family Security Matters is a conservative website affiliated with Frank Gaffneys conspiracy think tank the Center for Security Policy. Although this source does embrace conspiracies involving Islam; it is more of an extreme right wing news source. (11/19/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "http://federalistpress.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "The Federalist Press is a news and opinion website with strong right bias in reporting and wording. Not always sourced well; but does report factual newsmore often than not with a variety of loaded words. (8/10/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.foxnews.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "Fox News Channel; also known as Fox News; is an American basic cable and satellite news television channel that is owned by the Fox Entertainment Group subsidiary of 21st Century Fox. Fox News Channel has been accused of biased reporting and promoting the Republican Party and has been deemed the least accurate cable news source according to Politifact. (7/19/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.freedomworks.org/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "FreedomWorks is a conservative and libertarian advocacy group based in Washington D.C.; United States. FreedomWorks trains volunteers; assists in campaigns; and encourages them to mobilize; interacting with both fellow citizens and their political representatives. It is widely associated with the Tea Party movement. Right wing bias in reporting and some campaign ads have not been factual. (6/19/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.futureinamerica.com/news", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "Future in America is a conservative Super PAC that also publishes highly biased right wing news that is not always 100% factual. (11/7/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "https://www.gatestoneinstitute.org/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "The Gatestone Institute; formerly Stonegate Institute; is a not-for-profit international policy council and think tank based in New York City with a specialization in strategy and defense issues.Gatestone Institute is anti-Islamic; pro-Christian and Jewish/Israel. Many of the articles will link back to sites that dont say what they claim or make the same rash judgments; without proof. Example: Obama tells Christians to not protest in Egypt then has no quotes or sources saying he said that. (M. Allen 12/30/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "https://www.gop.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "GOP.com is a website paid for by the Republican National Committee (RNC). They report party news and have a blog that covers policy news and updates on what prominent political figures in the party are saying and advocating for. The website is very professional in appearance and uses minimal loaded words. GOP.comtypically sources to credible information; but they also report statements from politicians that may not be factual (see fact checkers for individual statements). Due to this we give them a mixed rating for factual reporting. (D. Van Zandt 2/24/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.g-a-i.org/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "The Government Accountability Institute (GAI) is a conservative nonprofit investigative research organization located in Tallahassee; Florida.GAI was founded in 2012. Has a right wing bias in reporting and generally sources to legit info; but will cherry pick to confirm their bias. (8/1/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "https://www.heartland.org/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "The Heartland Institute is an American conservative and libertarian public policy think tank founded in 1984. The Institute conducts work on issues including education reform; government spending; taxation; healthcare; education; tobacco policy; global warming; hydraulic fracturing; information technology; and free-market environmentalism. The Heartland Institute became a leading supporter of climate change denial.It rejects the scientific consensus on global warming;and says that policies to fight it would be damaging to the economy. They are heavily funded by corporations involved in the fossil fuel industry. Heartland Institute has been found to be false on occasion. (7/19/2016) Updated (4/5/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.heritage.org/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "The Heritage Foundation is an American conservative think tank based in Washington; D.C. The foundation took a leading role in the conservative movement during the presidency of Ronald Reagan; whose policies were taken from Heritages policy study Mandate for Leadership.Heritage has since continued to have a significant influence in U.S. public policy making; and is considered to be one of the most influential conservative research organizations in the United States. Occasionally; uses loaded words and does not always source to credible information. Has been put on a list by the Union of Concerned Scientists for publishing misleading information regarding climate change. (7/19/2016) Updated (4/22/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://heatst.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "Heat Street is a conservative opinion and commentary website. Launched in February 2016; the website is headed by British writer and former politician Louise Mensch.It is owned by News Corp under Dow Jones & Company. This source has a right wing bias through wording and story selection. Heat Street was also one of the sources Donald Trump quoted for his debunked claim that his phone was wiretapped by Obama. (11/21/2016) Updated (4/5/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http:/hotair.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "Hot Air is a conservative American political blog. It is written by the pseudonymous Allahpundit; Ed Morrissey; John Sexton; and Jazz Shaw. Hot Air was founded by Michelle Malkin; a conservative author and blogger; in 2006. The writers vary in biases; but all are to the right. While the source is certainly biased we could not find evidence of failed fact checks and most articles are reasonably sourced. (7/19/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.hudson.org/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "The Hudson Institute is an American conservative non-profit think tank based in Washington; D.C.. It was founded in 1961 in Croton-on-Hudson; New York; by futurist; military strategist; and systems theorist Herman Kahn and his colleagues at the RAND Corporation. Has right wing bias in reporting and story choices. Well sourced. (7/19/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "http://humanevents.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "An online conservative magazine. Regular writers have included Robert Novak; Ann Coulter; Terence P. Jeffrey; Pat Buchanan; and John Gizzi; its chief political editor. Occasional contributors have included Sean Hannity; Newt Gingrich; and Paul Craig Roberts; and Cliff Kincaid. Human Events has a right bias based on story selection and wording that favors conservatives. They have also published false information such as this article Why Martin Luther King Was Republican; which is false according to Politifact. (8/16/2016) Updated (4/5/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "https://ijr.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "The Independent Journal Review is an American news website founded in 2012. It has over 35 million visitors a month; making it one of the top fifty websites in the United States. Has significant right wing biasthrough story selection that favors conservatives and is against liberals. Occasionally uses loaded words in headlines and articles; but tends to source to mostly credible information. Has not been reviewed for any false claims through the major fact checkers. (8/19/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.independentsentinel.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "According the Independent Sentinels about page they provides news; opinion and commentary; analysis; factual and original content; mostly political; usually right-of-center; for aConservative; Libertarian; Republican audience. Our review of theIndependent Sentinel revealsa right wing biased website based on reporting choices that are one sided. Most headlines are sensationalized with loaded words; positive towards the right and negative toward the left. While the Independent Sentinel does produce real news and they usuallycite credible sources; there are some articles that citefar right sources such as Breitbart. However; we were unable to find an instance where the Independent Sentinel failed a fact check.We rate the Independent Sentinel right biased with mostlyfactual reporting. (D. Van Zandt 3/14/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.jewishworldreview.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "Jewish World Review is a free; online magazine updated Monday through Friday.It carries informational articles related to Judaism; dozens of syndicated columns written mostly by politically conservative writers; both Jewish and Gentile; advice columns on a number of issues; and cartoons. Jewish World Review has a right wing conservative bias in story selection and many times does not properly source information in articles. For example; in the article entitled: REVEALED: The Obama administrations support for Hamas was not passive; there is not a single link to an external source to support the claim that Obama actively supported Hamas. Further; the author of this piece is from the Dave Horowitz Freedom Center; which is a far right wing anti-islam organization. (D. Van Zandt)"),
new Bias(source: "https://judicialnetwork.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "The Judicial Crisis Network (JCN) (originally founded as the Judicial Confirmation Network) is an American conservative political campaign organization based in the United States. As of 2014 it was run by Carrie Severino; a former law clerk for Supreme Court Justice Clarence Thomas. In January; JCN launched a 10 million dollar campaign to support Donald Trumps supreme court nominee. On the website they report news about the judicial system with a strong right wing bias through the use of loaded words and linking to other right biased sources."),
new Bias(source: "http://www.judicialwatch.org/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "Judicial Watch is a conservative educational foundation that promotes transparency; accountability and integrity in government; politics and the law. Unfortunately; Judicial Watch is not always accountable and publishes false information according to Politifact and Snopes. (7/19/2016) Updated (2/25/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://knoxreport.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "The Knox Report is a highly biased conservative source thatuses loaded words and sometimes does not source to credible information. This is mostly an opinion website and therefore has mixed factual rating."),
new Bias(source: "http://legalinsurrection.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "Legal Insurrection is a conservative blog created byWilliam A. Jacobson who is an American lawyerandprofessor. Legal Insurretion usesa good deal of loaded language in its headlines and within its articles. Their articles/commentaries are mainly from right wing sources and bloggers giving opinions on current news. (F.Locke Siewert 2/10/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://libertyalliance.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "Liberty Alliance; LLC is a private United States company with its headquarters in Atlanta; Georgia which operates a collection of conservative and Christianwebsites. Outside of hosting overtly right wing websites they also host a fair share of conspiracy sites. Liberty Alliance is also on the Politifact fake news list."),
new Bias(source: "http://libertyhangout.org/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "Liberty Hangout is a libertarian news and opinion website. Has a typical economic right wing bias and moderate left social bias. It uses loaded words; but not overtly. It typically sources information; but sometimes to far right or non-credible sources. (12/14/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "http://libertynews.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "A news and opinion website that has extreme right wing bias in reporting and does not always source facts well. Takes conservative positions such as being opposed to a minimum wage andagainst equal rights for LGBT. Sometimes promotes conspiracies."),
new Bias(source: "http://libertytalk.fm/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "LibertyTalk.FM is a website that connects people to live streams of right wing talk shows. All shows have a strong right wing bias and some are conspiracy shows such as the Alex Jones Show."),
new Bias(source: "http://libertyunyielding.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "Liberty Unyielding is a website that publishes original content as well as aggregated news from other sources. All original content has a strong right wing bias. Aggregated content is dependent on the source. (11/18/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "https://lifeandabout.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "Life and About is a news and opinion blog with a borderline extreme right bias in reporting. The tagline for this website is The Right Side of Life and indeed that is the only side they cover. This website does not have an about page or any information on the author Stephanie Norton. While Life and About does use sourcing of information; we found that some of the sources were from the far right or questionable category. Based on this we rate this source right biased with mixed factual reporting based on poor sourcing."),
new Bias(source: "http://www.lifenews.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "Life News is a news and opinion websitethat is focused on Pro-Life issues. They havea far right political bias and occasionally uses loaded words. They also source to other right wing biased or pseudoscience sources. (2/1/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "https://www.lifesitenews.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "LifeSiteNews is a non-profit Internet service dedicated to issues of culture; life; and family. The website was founded by the Campaign Life Coalition which has afar right bias. Both sources are anti-abortion and opposed to gay marriage."),
new Bias(source: "http://www.lifezette.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "LifeZette is an American news; opinion; and commentary website based in Washington; D.C.. It was founded in 2015 by conservative pundit and radio host Laura Ingraham. Typical right wing bias in reporting and wording. (10/5/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "http://louderwithcrowder.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "Louder with Crowder is a podcast; radio show and website run bySteven Blake Crowderwho is a Canadian-American conservative political commentator; actor; and comedian.We will focus on the website as that is what is available to check. The website has headlines that are loaded with sensationalism such as: Dear Violent Liberal Rioters: YOU Are the Fascist Nazis!. Within this article there is not a single link to an outside credible source. Every link; links to another Louder With Crowder article;which is a red flag for a credible source. Steven Crowder also had a mostly false claim with Snopes. When reading information from Steven Crowder one should keep in mind he is a comedian and take his information with a grain of salt. This is not a source to be used in a rational argument. (D. Van Zandt 3/3/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.unionleader.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "Daily newspaper from Manchester; New Hampshire. Reports news factually; but has a very strong right wing editorial bias. (7/19/2016?"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.mrc.org/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "The Media Research Center (MRC) is a politically conservative content analysis organization based in Reston; Virginia; founded in 1987 by activist L. Brent Bozell III.Its stated mission is to provethrough sound scientific researchthat liberal bias in the media does exist and undermines traditional American values. Unfortunately; this source needs its content analyzed as it is very biased toward the right. They also advocate for climate denialism and even appear not to be on board with evolution. (7/19/2016) Updated (4/24/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.nationalreview.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "National Review (NR) is a semi-monthly magazine founded by author William F. Buckley; Jr. in 1955. Although the print version of the magazine is available online to subscribers; the free content on the website is essentially a separate publication under different editorial direction.The online version; National Review Online; describes itself as Americas most widely read and influential magazine and web site for conservativenews; commentary; and opinion. Has a right wing bias in reporting; but is well sourced and mostly factual with news."),
new Bias(source: "https://home.nra.org/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "The National Rifle Association of America (NRA) is an American nonprofit organization which advocates for gun rights. Observers and lawmakers see the NRA as one of the top three most influential lobbying groups in Washington. The NRA has a right wing bias as it supports Republican candidates and alleges that Democrats are attempting to restrict gun rights. The NRA has a mixed track record with Politifact."),
new Bias(source: "http://www.newsbusters.org/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "Newbusters claims to expose liberal bias much like its parent website MRC; however this site is also very right wing biased like MRC and perhaps even less factual. Newsbusters uses extensive loaded words and always covers just one side of the story. That side always benefits conservatives and is against liberals. (7/19/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.newsmax.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "Newsmax Media; commonly called Newsmax; is an American news media organization founded by Christopher Ruddy and based in West Palm Beach; Florida. It operates a multiplatform network focused onconservative-leaningmedia; including the news website Newsmax.com; publishes the Franklin Prosperity Report and Newsmax magazine; and the cable news channel Newsmax TV. This sourcehas a right wing bias in reporting and wording. Mostly factual and sourced news; but sometimes takes news out of context and is therefore mixed for factual reporting."),
new Bias(source: "http://www.newrevolutionnow.org/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "According the About pageNew Revolution Now is a non-profit; party-neutral organization created to support and advocate for core foundational American principles. Our Institute performs educational activities; outreach and organizing; legislative activism and endorsement. Their goals as stated on the website is to harness thecoreconservativevaluesofmainstream AmericanstoelectthestateandUS congressionalrepresentativeswhowillreturn thecountrytoitsfoundingvaluesof limitedgovernment;lowtaxation;statesrights; andconstitutionalconstructionism. This source really doesnt publish news; but it has a strong right wing political bias through its endorsement of conservative candidates."),
new Bias(source: "http://nextnewsnetwork.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "Next News Network was founded by radical Zionist Gary Franchi as an alternative news source. This source has strong pro-Israel bias and right wing bias with American politics. (11/8/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "https://www.numbersusa.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "NumbersUSA is an immigration reduction organization that seeks to reduce US immigration levels to pre-1965 levels without country of origin quotas as established in the Immigration Act of 1924. NumbersUSA was founded by Roy Beck while he worked for anti-immigration activist John Tanton; who has been described as a racist. NumbersUSA is also connected to the Federation for American Immigration Reform and the Center for Immigration studies; via John Tanton. Both of these groups are considered to beracist organizations; however; NumbersUSA does not promote against immigration from Non-Eurocentric countries. We therefore rate them Right Biased based on their political affiliation; rather than Questionable."),
new Bias(source: "http://www.oann.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "Originally envisioned as a conservative-oriented news network;OANs stated focus is delivering a credible source of national and international news 24/7.OAN features news programming and political talk shows; along with network special documentary-style reports. Its news coverage attempts to maintain objectivity while its political talk shows illustrate a strong conservative view. Unfortunately; this source also occasionally promotes conspiracies. (10/12/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.onenewsnow.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "OneNewsNow is a news and opinion website with a very strong Christian Right bias. OneNewsNow publishes unscientific news stories and does not source to legitimate sources. They do post some serious news that is not related to politics; that is fairly balanced. (12/15/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "https://pjmedia.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "PJ Media (originally known as Pajamas Media) is an American online media company and operator of an eponymous conservative news; opinion and commentary collaborative blog that was founded in 2004. Has a right wing bias in reporting and content. PJ Media has also made some questionable claims."),
new Bias(source: "http://www.hoover.org/publications/policy-review", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "No longer published as of 2013."),
new Bias(source: "http://www.thepoliticalinsider.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "A political news and opinion website with a strong conservative bias. Can be unreliablefor facts and sometimes publishes right wing conspiracy theories. This source is very close to the questionable list and needs to be fact checked. It has also landed on Politifacts fake news list."),
new Bias(source: "http://politichicks.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "Politichicks is a very conservative right wing web tv show. Does not shy from right wing conspiracies and may require fact checking from credible sources on certain stories. Refers to liberals as Snowflakes right in the headlines. We rate this source mixed for factual reporting based on getting information from far right and questionable sources."),
new Bias(source: "http://www.powerlineblog.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "Power Line is an Americanconservativepolitical blog; founded in May 2002. Power Line often vigorously criticizes Democrats and liberals for dishonesty; lack of morals; bad judgment and disloyalty to the United States. While this source has a very strong right wing opinion bias they do report news with proper sources. (10/30/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "http://projectveritas.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "Project Veritas was created byJames Edward OKeefe IIIwho is an American conservative political activist.He produces secretly recorded undercover audio and video encounters; some selectively edited to imply its subjects said things they did not;with figures and workers in academic; governmental and social service organizations; purporting to show abusive or allegedly illegal behavior by employees and/or representatives of those organizations. Project Veritas primarily targets liberals and liberal organizations. OKeefes videos are edited in a way that makes them difficult to fact check. Often his information is debunked; but it is too late as the information has already been watched by thousands or more. See RationalWiki for more on James OKeefe. (11/16/2016) Updated (4/26/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://redalertpolitics.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "Red Alert Politics states that it is an online publication written by young conservatives for young conservatives. It is published by MediaDC; which also publishes The Weekly Standard and The Washington Examiner. This source has a right wing bias in reporting and wording. It is average for sourcing and is moderately trustworthy for accuracy of information.(12/8/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.redflagnews.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "Red Flag News is a news and opinion website that reports with far right wing bias. Although they do publish real news; many stories are not properly sourced or are simply conspiracy theories. Has a questionablefact checking record."),
new Bias(source: "http://www.redstate.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "Red State is a news opinion blog run by Erick Erickson; a TV and radio commentator.The information on the blog has loaded language and is right biased based on story selection. Erick Erickson does not have a great track record with fact checkers."),
new Bias(source: "http://redstatewatcher.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "Red State Watcher is a conservative news website that has strong right wing bias in reporting choices. While Red State Watcher does source its stories they almost always favor the right and discredit the left. In other words it is one sided. So; while this website might have a strong right wing bias; they are actually sourcing to mostly mainstream sources and hence we can give a high factual rating; but it must be navigated though a lot of bias."),
new Bias(source: "https://regated.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "Regated news is a news and opinion website with a right wing bias in reporting. Sometimes publishes poorly sourced news."),
new Bias(source: "http://www.resistancemedia.org/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "Resistance Media is a news and opinion website that focuses on public school reform; government transparency and family rights. The writerschoose to remain anonymousso they are automatically discredited as a legitimate source. Resistance Media is a far right biased news source that advocates for right wing political objectives such as limited immigration and anti-LGBTQ legislation. Some information is sourced well while others are sourced to highly questionable sources such as The Federation for American Immigration Reform (FAIR); which according to the Southern Poverty Law Center has ties to white supremacists. We would also like to point out that this source considers the SPLC as a corrupt liberal organization against white people. Another interesting aspect of this website is the FAQ page. Amazingly; two frequently asked questions are: Are you a racist? and Why do you hate gay people? One has to wonder why people are frequently asking those questions. Based on borderline extreme bias and using sources that are questionable we rate them mixed for factual reporting."),
new Bias(source: "http://www.ronpaullibertyreport.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "The Ron Paul Liberty Reportis a website and video programcreated by former Republican (Libertarian)Congressman Ron Paul. The LibertyReport advocates for a non-interventionist foreign policy and the protection of civil liberties at home. The Liberty Report generally reports with minimal loaded words and most times sources to credible information. However; there are times that they source to far right; questionable or conspiracy websites. They also occasionally publish unsubstantiated claims such as the Syria chemical attack being a false flag operation. (5/4/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.secureamericanow.org/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "Secure America Now (SAN) is a politically conservative nonprofit group that focuses on United States foreign policy issues. It says its mission is to raise security issues to the forefront of the American debate (Wikpedia). Has a blog section that presents news with a right wingpolitical bias and has a mostly false rating according to Politifact."),
new Bias(source: "http://silenceisconsent.net/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "Silence is Consent is a right wing news and opinion website.This sources uses strong loaded words and typically only publishes one side of the story. While there is certainly effort to source information in the articles; they sometimes source to far right or questionable sources according to our ratings."),
new Bias(source: "http://spiked-online.com/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "Spiked is a British Internet magazine focusing on politics; culture and society from a libertarian viewpoint.Spiked focuses on issues of freedom and state control; science and technology; culture; education and literature. Has a moderate right wing bias in reporting and does not support the consensus of science on environmental issues.(12/27/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.westernjournalism.com/thepoint/", factuality: "MIXED", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "Tea Party News is now called The Point and is hosted by Western Journalism.The website still has farright wing biased contentthat utilizes strong loaded words against liberalism. Does not shy from conspiracy theories such as Hillary Clinton having Parkinsons Disease. (7/19/2016) Updated (4/6/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.teapartypatriots.org/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "Tea Party Patriots is a conservative American political organization that promotes fiscally responsible activism as part of the Tea Party movement. The Tea Party Patriots website provides news related to the Tea Party and conservative/libertarian politics. Articles have minimal loaded words and most are well sourced and factually based."),
new Bias(source: "http://www.teapartytribune.com/", factuality: "HIGH", biasType: "Right Bias", notes: "The Tea Party Tribune is news and opinion site that has a right wing bias in reporting choices. TPT primary covers conservative politics that is in line with the Tea Party platform. While many articles certainly have a strong right wing bias in word selection; most are reasonably sourced to credible websites and information. (7/19/2016)"),
