new Bias(source: "https://ageofshitlords.com/", factuality: "N/A", biasType: "Questionable Sources", notes: "Age of Shitlords is a news and opinion website that is adamantly opposed to feminism. On the other hand it also writes many satire articles which generally makes this website confusing. We are listing it as questionable because it is difficult to tell what is real and what is meant to be satire. (5/13/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://alabamaobserver.com/", factuality: "N/A", biasType: "Questionable Sources", notes: "The Alabama Observer is website that is attempting to look like a real Alabama Newspaper. They publish a combination of real and fake news. The Alabama Observer is on Politifacts Fake News List. (6/7/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "http://allenwestrepublic.com/", factuality: "N/A", biasType: "Questionable Sources", notes: "A website created by a fan of Allen West. The website publishes information about Allen West and also highly biased right wing news stories. This source produces propaganda and has a poor track record with facts since it reports about Allen West. (10/4/2016) Updated (6/19/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://allnewspipeline.com/", factuality: "N/A", biasType: "Questionable Sources", notes: "All News Pipeline (ANP) is a news and opinion blog that publishes news with an extreme right wing bias.The articles reviewed today from their news section reveal a severe distrust of mainstream media. In fact; most articles reference MSM as being fake news. This is ironic as ANP has false claims as indicated by Snopes. ANP also has a category called Alternative News that publishes tin foil hat conspiracies. This source has it all; extreme right bias; propaganda; poorly sourced and heavy on conspiracy theories. (5/16/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "http://alternativemediasyndicate.com", factuality: "N/A", biasType: "Questionable Sources", notes: "The Alternative Media Syndicate is a news and opinion website/blog that has an extreme left wing bias. Presents information with moderate loaded words and sometimes links to questionable sources. Has a very strong liberal bias in story selection and does not have an about page.According to Snopes has published a false news story. They also have a Pants of Fire rating from Politifact. (2/7/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "https://www.acpeds.org/", factuality: "N/A", biasType: "Questionable Sources", notes: "The American College of Pediatricians (ACPeds) is an advocacy group of pediatricians and other healthcare professionals in the United States.The group was founded in 2002 by a group of pediatricians; including Joseph Zanga; a past president of the American Academy of Pediatrics (AAP); as a protest against the AAPs support for adoption by gay couples.The groups membership as of 2016 is estimated at 500 members;in contrast to the AAPs over 60;000 members. The organizations view on parenting is at odds with the position of the American Academy of Pediatrics; which holds that sexual orientation has no correlation with the ability to be a good parent and to raise healthy and well-adjusted children.The American College of Pediatricians has been described by the Southern Poverty Law Center as a hate group; with a history of propagating damaging falsehoods about LGBT people. (4/15/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.americanpatriotdaily.com/", factuality: "N/A", biasType: "Questionable Sources", notes: "American Patriot Daily is a news and opinion blog with an extreme right wing bias in reporting. All stories use loaded words that favor conservatives and denigrate liberals. They consistently only present one side of the story; which misrepresents facts. This is a classic propaganda tactic that uses just enough facts to make a case; without providing a counter point to give full context. The American Daily Patriot does tend to source their articles; however our review shows that they mostly use right wing sources such as Breitbart and Daily Caller; both of which have made false claims according to fact checkers. (5/22/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.afa.net/", factuality: "N/A", biasType: "Questionable Sources", notes: "The American Family Association (AFA) is a non-profit organization based in the United States that promotes fundamentalist Christian values. It opposes same-sex marriage; pornography; and abortion. The AFA is considers an anti-LGBT hate group by the Southern Poverty Law Center. Not well sourced. (1/13/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://americanflavor.news/", factuality: "N/A", biasType: "Questionable Sources", notes: "American Flavor is a news and opinion site with an extreme right wing bias. This site does not have an about page describing it as satire; so we must assume this is a fake news website. Has incredible stories such as BREAKING: Christianity Ruled Illegal! This source is also listed on Politifacts Fake News List. (6/7/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.americasfreedomfighters.com/", factuality: "N/A", biasType: "Questionable Sources", notes: "Americas Freedom Fighters is a news and opinion website that has over the top right wing bias. Routinely publishes conspiracy theories and is not always factual.(11/22/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "https://americanlookout.com/", factuality: "N/A", biasType: "Questionable Sources", notes: "American Lookout is a conservative news and opinion site. Has a very strong to extreme right wing bias and does not source to credible information. Considers credible news sources to be fake news. Promotes propaganda. (11/23/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "http://americannews.com/", factuality: "N/A", biasType: "Questionable Sources", notes: "American News is an extreme right wing biased news and opinion site. Poorly sourced with minimal basis in facts. (8/9/2016) Updated (6/19/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://americanpeoplenetwork.com/", factuality: "N/A", biasType: "Questionable Sources", notes: "The American People Network is a news and opinion website with an extreme right wing bias in reporting. APN does not always source their information and when they do it is often to other far right sources. There is use of loaded words in both headlines and articles. This source is also hosted in Macedonia; which is famous for operating far right fake news websites. APN is also flagged by Politifact as being a purveyor of fake news. (6/7/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.amren.com/", factuality: "N/A", biasType: "Questionable Sources", notes: "American Renaissance (AR or AmRen) is a monthly online magazine published by the New Century Foundation which describes itself as a race-realist; white advocacy organization.It has been described as awhite supremacist publication by several sources; including The Washington Post; Fortune; and the Anti-Defamation League. According to the Southern Poverty Law Center ARis a self-styled think tank that promotes pseudo-scientific studies and research that purport to show the inferiority of blacks to whites  although in language that avoids open racial slurs and attempts to portray itself as serious scholarship. (10/6/2016) Updated (6/26/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://americantoday.news/", factuality: "N/A", biasType: "Questionable Sources", notes: "American Today is a news and opinion blog with an extreme right wing bias. Every headline and article contains loaded emotional words that favor conservatives and discredits liberals. Further; 90% of the articles reviewed were pro-Trump propaganda; that though linked to evidence; did not present the other side of the story from a different perspective. American Today is also listed as an Untrustworthy website by Fake News Checker. (5/22/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://americanupdater.com/", factuality: "N/A", biasType: "Questionable Sources", notes: "American Updater is a news and opinion website with extreme right bias. Publishes common right wing conspiracies such as claiming President Obama is the Anti-Christ.Many stories are simply fake news. (10/3/2016) Updated (6/19/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://aattp.org/", factuality: "N/A", biasType: "Questionable Sources", notes: "Americans Against the Tea Party is a news and opinion website that was created in response to the rise of the Tea Party. Their mission is to dispel the falsehoods and myths spread by conservatives. Unfortunately; they produce content that is highly sensationalized and poorly sourced. AATTP is the far lefts response to right wing propaganda and it is equally as bad. It appears AATTP stopped publishing in July 2016. (3/24/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://aurora-news.us/", factuality: "N/A", biasType: "Questionable Sources", notes: "Aurora-News is a news and opinion blog with an extreme right wing bias in reporting. A-N used loaded words in headlines and the majority of the articles favors conservatives over liberals. This source is also listed on Politifacts fake news listas an imposter site. (6/9/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "https://www.avoiceformen.com/", factuality: "N/A", biasType: "Questionable Sources", notes: "A Voice for Men (AVFM) is a mens human right advocacy site run by Paul Elam; the titular leader of the mens rights movement in America. AVFM is not so much a news source as an extended blog and echo chamber consisting primarily of op-ed style content decrying the feminist movement and touting what Mr. Elam and other contributors see as the persecution of males in a female run society. There is very little external sourcing for any of the content; and what source links I did follow led only to other anti-feminism opinion pieces and sites. The content is heavily weighted against feminism; and much of it revolves around the usual mens rights issues. Divorce; custody; child support; mens reproductive rights; etc. The site earns a Questionable rating based on the extreme bias of its mens rights advocacy. (D. Kelley 3/4/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://bb4sp.com/", factuality: "N/A", biasType: "Questionable Sources", notes: "BB4SP is an online news and opinion source. The site consists of extreme right wing news; some conspiracy and uses racial terms such asThug to describe African Americans.This source does not source information well. BB4SP has been placed on Politifacts Fake News List. (9/22/2016) Updated (6/26/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://beforeitsnews.com/", factuality: "N/A", biasType: "Questionable Sources", notes: "Before Its News is a citizens journalism website where stories are provided by individuals without credentials. Stories can range from moderately credible to tin-foil hat conspiracies. It seems this source has become a haven for conspiracy theorists and pseudo-scientists. Further; the website is riddled with pop-up ads and potential malware that make it impossible and unsafe to navigate. This source has been classified as Fake News by Fake News Watchand Politifact. (7/20/2016) Updated (6/19/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://bigbluevision.org/", factuality: "N/A", biasType: "Questionable Sources", notes: "Big Blue Vision is an extreme right biased news source. They do not shy from conspiracies and virtually everything they report has factual issues due to lack of credible sources. (12/19/2016) Updated (6/26/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.bipartisanreport.com/", factuality: "N/A", biasType: "Questionable Sources", notes: "The Bipartisan Report is a news and opinion website with a very clear and extremeliberal bias. The BP uses strong loaded language in both sensational headlines and also the body of articles. BP has published articles containingpseudoscience and conspiracies. They also have a poor track record with fact checkers here and here. BP is a liberal propaganda website that requires fact checking. (5/13/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.blackgenocide.org/home.html", factuality: "N/A", biasType: "Questionable Sources", notes: "Black Genocide is a radical anti-abortion website that promotes the idea that Blacks have been targeted to have abortions. This site relies on very old debunked conspiracies and consistently fails in fact checking."),
new Bias(source: "http://bluevision.news/", factuality: "N/A", biasType: "Questionable Sources", notes: "BlueVision.News is a news and opinion website with an extreme right bias in reporting. Most stories are either fake or highly misleading. BlueVision.News is listed as a fake news site according to Politifact. ( 6/12/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://bluevisionpost.com/", factuality: "N/A", biasType: "Questionable Sources", notes: "Blue Vision Post is a news and opinion website with an extreme right bias in reporting. Most stories are either fake or highly misleading. Blue Vision Post is listed as a fake news site according to Politifact. (6/12/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.censored.news/", factuality: "N/A", biasType: "Questionable Sources", notes: "Censored.News aggregates news from a variety of sources. Virtually every one of them is either Questionable; Conspiracy; Pseudoscience by our standards and all have a right wing bias. For example; they have an entire newsfeed dedicated to Natural News and well known purveyor of right wing conspiracies and pseudoscience. (4/14/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://cis.org/", factuality: "N/A", biasType: "Questionable Sources", notes: "The Center for Immigration Studies (CIS) is a non-profit research organization that favors far lower immigration numbers and produces research to further those views.It was started as a spin-off from John TantonsFederation for American Immigration Reform (FAIR) in 1985.Reports published by the CIS have been widely deemed misleading and riddled with basic errors by scholars on immigration; think tanks from across the ideological and political spectrum; media of all stripes; several leading nonpartisan immigration-research organizations; and by U.S. Immigration and Customs Enforcement. The organization has also drawn criticism for its financial and intellectual ties to extremist racists.The Southern Poverty Law Center (SPLC) published reports in 2002and 2009connecting CIS to John Tanton; who helped found various other organizations; including the Federation for American Immigration Reform (FAIR) and NumbersUSA; and showing he has ties to white supremacy groups and a eugenics foundation (SPLC). Bottom line; this is a hate group. (2/8/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://cityworldnews.com/", factuality: "N/A", biasType: "Questionable Sources", notes: "CityWorldNews is a fake news and opinion website. According to SnopesCityWorldNews is a fake news web site that does not publish factual stories: the front page of the site currently lists hoax stories about Jeb Bushs entering a mental hospital; a fake Donald Trump tweet; and a womans desire to raise her youngest daughter as a stripper. (3/15/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "https://clarionproject.org/", factuality: "N/A", biasType: "Questionable Sources", notes: "The Clarion Project (formerly Clarion Fund Inc.) is a Washington; D.C.-based non-profit organization founded in 2006.The Clarion Project states its mission as exposing the dangers of Islamic extremism while providing a platform for the voices of moderation and promoting grassroots activism. The Clarion Project has an extreme right wing bias in reporting and wording. They are classified as an active anti-Muslim hate group by the Southern Poverty Law Center. Has a false claim according to a fact checker. (4/15/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://clashdaily.com/", factuality: "N/A", biasType: "Questionable Sources", notes: "Clash Daily is a website founded by Doug Giles; an extreme christian right pastor. The content of the website is extreme right wing that often is not factual; unscientific and biased. It demonstrates oppositiontoward LGBT people; atheists and Muslims through wording and political affiliation. Clash Daily is on Politifacts Fake News List. (10/19/2016) Updated (6/19/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://cnn.com.de/", factuality: "N/A", biasType: "Questionable Sources", notes: "Fake News website that looks similar to CNN. (1/24/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.cnn-globalnews.com/", factuality: "N/A", biasType: "Questionable Sources", notes: "Cnn-GlobalNews.com is an imposter website that is attempting to look like CNN International. The website uses a similar logo and color theme. However; one look at the lead story reveals that it is fake. They are reporting on the death of Actor/Director Clint Eastwood; which was a hoax in May of 2017. Not a credible source. (6/20/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "https://conservativedailypost.com/", factuality: "N/A", biasType: "Questionable Sources", notes: "The Conservative Daily Post is a news and opinion website that is hard to determine if it is satire or real. If it is real then it is off the charts with right wing propaganda and conspiracy. Others have classified this website as fake news. Has a poor record with both Snopes and Politifact. Was recently added to Politifacts Fake News List. (11/4/2016) Updated (6/19/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://conservativefighters.com/", factuality: "N/A", biasType: "Questionable Sources", notes: "Conservative Fighters is a news and opinion website that does not source to credible sources; if at all. The bias is extreme right and uses questionable language regardingrace. For every credible article there seems to be twothat are conspiracy or propaganda. (1/20/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "https://www.conservativeinfocorner.us/", factuality: "N/A", biasType: "Questionable Sources", notes: "Conservative Info Corner is a news and opinion website that has extreme right wing bias and often publishes fake news. For example; they have an article claiming that Malia Obama was expelled from Harvard due to drug use. According to Snopes this is False. In another story there is a headline that reads Barack Obama Resurfaces to make Terrifying Announcement this isnt good. This misleading/sensational headline then takes you to a story about how Obama is going to speak in Ireland. That is it. Nothing terrifying. This is a fake news source. (4/12/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://conservativeflashnews.com/", factuality: "N/A", biasType: "Questionable Sources", notes: "Conservative Flash News is an extreme right wing website that publishes mostly fake news or extremely misleading stories. Virtually all stories are unsourced or linked to untrustworthy websites. According to Politifact this is a fake news source and we concur. (6/12/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://www.conservapedia.com/Main_Page", factuality: "N/A", biasType: "Questionable Sources", notes: "Conservapedia is an English-language wiki encyclopedia project written from an American conservative; Young Earth creationist; and Christian fundamentalist point of view. This website is not credible for science information and a lot of reports are simply false. (8/21/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "https://conservative101.com/", factuality: "N/A", biasType: "Questionable Sources", notes: "Conservative 101 is a news and opinion website with an extreme right wing bias. This source routinely publishes conspiracy theories and has been accused of publishing fake news. This source could easily be listed in our Conspiracy category; but because of its one sided right wing bias we will place it here. This websitehas zero credibility as a news source. (11/23/2016) Updated (6/19/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://conservativepost.com/", factuality: "N/A", biasType: "Questionable Sources", notes: "The Conservative Post is a news and opinion website with Extreme right wing/conservative bias in content and wording. Content is sometimes so over the top it is difficult to tell if it is serious or satire. Articles contain questionable languageregarding race and many are not factual. (7/18/2016) Updated (6/19/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://conservativespirit.com/", factuality: "N/A", biasType: "Questionable Sources", notes: "Conservative Spirit is an extreme right wing biased news and opinion website. A lot of information is factually inaccurate and they publish conspiracies such as the Clintons murdering people. This source is also on Politifacts Fake News List. (11/19/2016)"),
new Bias(source: "http://conservativetribune.com/", factuality: "N/A", biasType: "Questionable Sources", notes: "The Conservative Tribune displays blatant right wing/conservative bias. Consistently fails fact checks;glorifies violence against African Americans and Muslims and promotes right wing conspiracies. (7/18/2016) Updated (7/19/2017)"),
new Bias(source: "http://rickwells.us/", factuality: "N/A", biasType: "Questionable Sources", notes: "This is essentially a right wing blog with very strong conservative bias in reporting. Constitution Rising often makes conspiratorial claims without evidence such as this:Syria Attack  ISIS False Flag To Give Establishment Their War With Assad; Russia. This source could easily be listed in our Conspiracy/Pseudoscience category; but do to the extreme right bias we rate it as questionable. (10/19/2016)"),
